# Agent discovery — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

This project ships an **`ai-catalog.json`** so AI agents can *discover* its resources without
loading them up front. It follows the [Agentic Resource Discovery](https://agenticresourcediscovery.org/spec/)
(ARD) spec — the agent-facing companion to the project's open-knowledge (`knowledge/`) layer:
ARD advertises *what* is here and how to reach it; agents invoke each resource through its own
protocol (a skill runner, MCP, A2A, an API).

## What this project advertises

`ai-catalog.json` lists this project's discoverable resources as typed `entries`. By default it
advertises the project's **Markdown skills** (`application/ai-skill+md`). Add an entry for each
further resource you expose, using its IANA media type:

| Resource | `type` | `url` points at |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Markdown skill(s) (`.skills/`) | `application/ai-skill+md` | the skill / repo |
| Published dataset | e.g. `application/parquet`, `text/csv` | the data file or its landing page |
| MCP server | `application/mcp-server+json` | the server's MCP descriptor |
| A2A agent | `application/a2a-agent-card+json` | the agent card JSON |
| Nested catalog | `application/ai-catalog+json` | another `ai-catalog.json` |

Each entry needs a domain-anchored URN `identifier` (`urn:ai:{{ARD_HOST_DOMAIN}}:<namespace>:<name>`),
a `displayName`, the `type`, and either a `url` or embedded `data`. `capabilities` and
`representativeQueries` (2–5) make the resource findable by semantic search. Keep `updatedAt` current.

## Deploy across levels

- **Repo (now).** `ai-catalog.json` lives at the repository root and is version-controlled. This is
  the lowest discovery scope and needs no infrastructure.
- **Host / domain (later).** Serve the manifest at `https://{{ARD_HOST_DOMAIN}}/.well-known/ai-catalog.json`
  with `Content-Type: application/json` and `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *`, over HTTPS. Add a
  discovery pointer per the spec (a `robots.txt` `Agentmap:` directive or an HTML
  `<link rel="ai-catalog">`). Copy the repo file as the starting point.
- **Org / ecosystem registry (later).** Register the catalog with an enterprise or public registry
  (e.g. Hugging Face Discover, a Google Agent Registry), or run your own searchable endpoint
  (`POST /search` + federation) advertised as an `application/ai-registry+json` entry.

The host and registry steps are deployment work and are tracked in `ROADMAP.md` until you take them on.

## Trust & identity

URNs are anchored to `{{ARD_HOST_DOMAIN}}`, so publish only from a domain you control — the domain is
the trust anchor. `host.identifier` is set to `{{ARD_HOST_IDENTIFIER}}` (a `did:web` is conventional).
For stronger guarantees, add a `trustManifest` (verifiable identity / signatures) to entries per the spec.
